Super Eagles goalkeeper, Maduka Okoye, threw social media into frenzy immediately after the AFCON 3-1 win over Sudan on Saturday, with several Nigerian young ladies crushing on him, PUNCH Sports Extra reports. The 22-year-old 1.97m tall shot stopper was the talking point as a result of his physique. After the game against the Sudanese, several Nigerian guys criticised Okoye for his poor ball handling, but the ladies latched back in droves, in defence of the German-born keeper. A Twitter user with the name @AriesQueeeenn said, “I don’t care if Okoye did not catch penalty, as long as he catches me when I fall.” Grace Amankwah wrote “My fave Sunset in Lekki. Anyways Okoye dey enter my eye sha, abeg I close am ooooo.” Another lady with the name Edu tweeted, “Dear Maduka Okoye. Please don’t forget to apply balm on your shoulders, they would not kill you for us. Keep catching the ball gracefully. Ball can come and go but your drip is eternal.” Another big admirer of the goalkeeper with the name Na Ment said, “Me personally care about my baby Okoye than the match abeg.” “Wish I was there to save the penalty for Okoye.. See fine guy,” Bittersugar tweeted. Mary Bashua-Alimi simply said, “Maduka Okoye is hot though…” Eager to know of the 22-year-old status, @thelordknowskay asked, “Does Maduka Okoye have a girlfriend? Asking for research.” @babe_felicita said sahe would watch the match again to see Okoye, “That okoye is fine ooo. Face with tears of joy. I’m definitely going to rewatch that match to see him smile again.”  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com